title: Hermann Wine Trail: Seven Hills of Herman Ride
Mizzou Mountain Bike Race 2008 - XC
course: Held at Rockbridge Memorial State Park. Winding single track with lots of hills and a stream crossing. Laps are around 5.7 miles each.
directions: From east of Columbia, take I-70 West through Columbia to Highway 63 South. Exit off at Grindstone Parkway and head west. Turn left heading south onto Providence Road and turn left (east) onto 163 after two miles. Look for race signs and the entrance to Rockbridge State Park at the second curve.

title: Mizzou Mountain Bike Race 2008 - STXC/DS
description: Mizzou Short Track and Dual Slalom
course: The STXC course will be similar to past years. It will ahve some technical sections and cyclocross bikes will probably not survive or do well. The DS course will be similar to past years, and has been well maintained
directions: From College Ave. (runs north/south from BS70 to Stadium Blvd.), turn east when you get to Ashland Rd. From there, signs will be posted, directing you to a parking area and the STXC/DS course.

title: Hermann Cross Under the Lights Invitational
Subaru Short Track Dirt Crit Championship
Smithville Cyclo-cross Festival
description: The Riverside Cyclocross Festival takes place in the beautiful E. H. Young Riverfront Park. This will be the 8th year of our event. We will be hosting rounds 2 and 3 of the Kansas City Cross series.
course: Course is 1.75 miles long and includes a rocky staircase climb, sand pit, off-camber turns, short run-ups, plenty of pavement sections and a trip down to the Missouri River and back.
registration: Registration closes 15 minutes before each race. Racing license must be shown at registration. A one day license may be purchased for 10.00.
notes: USCF permit applied for. All USCF Cyclocross rules apply. ANSI approved helmets required for all events. Mountain bikes are allowed, but must have bar ends removed. Races held rain or shine A domestic USCF or NORBA license is required. Parking: Follow signs to parking.
directions: From Kansas City: take I-29 North to I-635, merge onto US-69 South. Turn left onto NW Frontage Rd., NW Frontage Rd becomes NW Tremont. Turn right onto NW Argosy Parkway. Follow signs to E.H. Young Riverfront Park.
